      "text": "Alarm Output\nClosed-loop drives should expose a fault output so\nthe controller or safety logic can stop coordinated\nmotion when one axis fails.",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 15.0,
      "containerId": "node-e232d1ed0b7c",
      "originalText": "Alarm Output\nClosed-loop drives should expose a fault output so the controller or safety logic can stop coordinated motion when one axis fails.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "autoResize": true,
      "customData": {
        "node_id": "alarm-output"
      }
    },
